age drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:52:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:64:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:66:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:103:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/overview.md](../forge/docs/overview.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:66:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:68:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:106:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:157:    \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:80:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:98:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:116:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:135:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:153:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:171:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:189:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:207:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:225:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynam